wait 'til later...

110
00:08:55,576 --> 00:08:57,412
{\an1}I have an important
mission in the morning.

111
00:08:57,445 --> 00:08:58,946
And I need to
prepare for it.

112
00:09:00,014 --> 00:09:01,983
You're such a
big fat liar.

113
00:09:08,891 --> 00:09:10,025
Sorry, Sasuke.

114
00:09:10,224 --> 00:09:11,727
{\an1}Maybe some other time.

115
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,028
Hmph!

116
00:09:14,596 --> 00:09:15,964
{\an1}Okay, just watch this!

117
00:09:16,598 --> 00:09:17,633
Hm?

118
00:09:17,933 --> 00:09:19,268
{\an1}Hey, be careful!

119
00:09:19,301 --> 00:09:20,502
[screaming]

120
00:09:33,850 --> 00:09:35,418
{\an1}Keep excelling like
this and you'll be

121
00:09:35,452 --> 00:09:37,387
just like your
brother in no time.

122
00:09:38,722 --> 00:09:44,929
{\an7}<i>Father... I wanted you to say...</i>
<i>"that's my boy"... to me...</i>

123
00:09:49,633 --> 00:09:53,804
{\an1}Such behavior is just a
process to help one mature!

124
00:09:53,839 --> 00:09:56,074
{\an1}Don't use it as a cloak to
deceive yourself, like

125
00:09:56,108 --> 00:09:57,142
you've done!

126
00:09:59,077 --> 00:10:01,179
{\an1}If you've attached your
self-value to something

127
00:10:01,213 --> 00:10:02,748
{\an1}external to you...

128
00:10:03,081 --> 00:10:05,617
{\an1}Even something admirable
and praiseworthy.

129
00:10:05,650 --> 00:10:07,220
{\an1}Then you gain nothing.

130
00:10:09,155 --> 00:10:10,923
I'll say this
one last time.

131
00:10:12,191 --> 00:10:15,293
{\an1}Don't mislead yourself with
lies. Those who cannot

132
00:10:15,327 --> 00:10:18,598
{\an1}acknowledge themselves
will invariably fail.

133
00:10:21,334 --> 00:10:22,335
Fail?!

134
00:10:23,237 --> 00:10:25,005
{\an1}The way I am now?

135
00:10:26,173 --> 00:10:28,341
{\an1}How could I fail?!

136
00:10:30,744 --> 00:10:32,679
Sasuke... Look
into my eyes!

137
00:10:32,913 --> 00:10:36,184
[gasp] That's
right! Of course!

138
00:10:36,217 --> 00:10:37,484
{\an1}Genjutsu! Sharingan!

139
00:10:37,518 --> 00:10:38,852
Tsukuyomi!

140
00:10:58,506 --> 00:11:01,442
{\an1}I shall now engage the
Izanami. Which means that

141
00:11:01,476 --> 00:11:04,513
{\an1}you have already failed.

142
00:11:09,852 --> 00:11:10,953
Is it over?

143
00:11:28,738 --> 00:11:31,075
{\an1}You, a genius that always
had everything, would never

144
00:11:31,108 --> 00:11:32,743
{\an1}understand at all...

145
00:11:33,277 --> 00:11:36,547
{\an1}The only thing I want is to
be who and what I am!

146
00:11:38,049 --> 00:11:40,918
{\an1}I won't let anyone
interfere!

147
00:11:56,401 --> 00:11:58,271
Sas... uke...

148
00:12:06,846 --> 00:12:08,414
{\an1}Fire Style: Fireball Jutsu!

149
00:12:09,316 --> 00:12:11,551
Water Style:
Giant Vortex Jutsu

150
00:12:18,558 --> 00:12:20,194
[groaning]

151
00:12:33,108 --> 00:12:34,376
[gasp]

152
00:12:51,526 --> 00:12:53,495
{\an1}You're just repeating
the same old moves.

153
00:12:53,829 --> 00:12:56,165
Makes it easier
for me to counter.

154
00:12:56,198 --> 00:12:58,734
{\an1}I already told you, with
this body I have the power

155
00:12:58,768 --> 00:13:01,570
{\an1}to recover from any wound
you try to inflict, so

156
00:13:01,604 --> 00:13:03,340
attacking me is
pointless.

157
00:13:04,107 --> 00:13:09,413
{\an1}Since I shut off my vision,
genjutsu won't work on me.

158
00:13:09,445 --> 00:13:11,915
You two have no
chance of winning.

159
00:13:11,949 --> 00:13:15,686
{\an1}Your fate is already
entirely in my hands.

160
00:13:15,719 --> 00:13:19,257
{\an1}All thanks to the Uchiha's
other Forbidden Jutsu.

161
00:13:20,158 --> 00:13:21,059
That is...

162
00:13:24,429 --> 00:13:25,296
Well, then...

163
00:13:26,431 --> 00:13:28,733
{\an1}Shall we put that boast of
yours to the test, Itachi?

164
00:13:32,036 --> 00:13:33,038
The Izanami!

165
00:13:36,976 --> 00:13:39,378
Sasuke... do not
leave my side.

166
00:13:42,381 --> 00:13:44,149
{\an1}This feels like déjà vu.

167
00:13:46,552 --> 00:13:47,853
{\an1}But you bore me...

168
00:13:48,321 --> 00:13:50,656
{\an1}So let's put an end to
this fight, already.

169
00:13:52,624 --> 00:13:55,028
{\an1}Your fate may be in
my hands now...

170
00:13:55,061 --> 00:13:57,364
{\an1}But only you can truly
decide how that fate

171
00:13:57,397 --> 00:13:58,631
{\an1}shapes your destiny.

172
00:14:01,268 --> 00:14:03,437
{\an1}Remember all that
I've told you.

173
00:14:04,472 --> 00:14:05,973
{\an1}You have to think hard.

174
00:14:07,574 --> 00:14:09,609
{\an1}Sorry, but I have
absolutely no idea

